    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-22T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-22T16:00:00-05:00" n="38"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense(M)Colombia/612: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-22T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 22, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>510. Department’s telegram 357, March 20, 7 p.m.<note n="66" xml:id="d38fn66">Not
                        printed.</note> Complete preliminary agreement has been reached with the
                    Minister of War<note n="67" xml:id="d38fn67">Presumably Ramon Santo Domingo, who
                        succeeded Alejandro Galvis Galvis on March 16, 1943.</note> on the air
                    rubber agreement based on terms conforming with the original contract submitted
                    by Defense Supplies Corporation. To <pb facs="0048" n="34" xml:id="pg_34"/>
                    simplify procedure Colombian authorities have considered it advisable to put
                    this agreement into effect as one of the individual steps to be taken in the
                    implementation of the more general agreement on strategic materials concerning
                    which the exchange of notes referred to in the Embassy’s telegram 495, March 19,
                    3 p.m.<note n="68" xml:id="d38fn68">Not printed.</note> and previous
                    correspondence is pending. It is expected that the air rubber agreement will be
                    made effective after such exchange of notes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
